The paper deals with a robotic manipulation task, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of reinforcement learning and Deep Q-learning (DQN) suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves image processing techniques to identify the target object, which could place it under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of the algorithm in a real environment suggests that it could also belong to the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
